### Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "meriem2004@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "firstName": "meriem",
  "lastName": "hamri"
}

### Login with existing user account
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "meriem2004@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}

### Refresh your session token (uses the cookie automatically)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh

### Logout to end your session
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout

### Get your current profile (You need to set @token above)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test: Register with an invalid email format
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "Password123",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith"
}

### Test: Register with a weak password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "password": "weak",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith"
}

### Test: Access admin data
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/admin
Content-Type: application/json 
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test: Register with an email that is already used
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Duplicate"
}

### Test: Login with a wrong password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword123"
}

### Test: Try to get profile without being logged in (no token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

### Test: Try to get profile with a fake token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here
